n fromthe sale of his stake.   Under terms of a settlement, De Benedetti's French investmentfirm Cerus SA will sell 7.75 million Societe Generale shares to arival Franco-Belgian group. Cerus currently owns 14.25 million ofmillion Societe Generale's 42 million outstanding shares.</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   U.S. trade sanctions imposed against SouthAfrica two years ago cut that nation's exports by about $417million, a loss South Africa was unable to recover by directingtrade to other countries, according to testimony before a Senatepanel.   A senior official of the General Accounting Office told theForeign Relations Committee on Friday that South Africa suffered asecond blow when it lost additional trade to 19 other major tradingpartners, resulting in a total trade reduction of $624 million ingoods sanctioned by the United States.</TEXT><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Stocks retreated Friday in moderate trading, asthe Dow Jones average of 30 industrial stocks fell 5.33 to 2,142.96.   The dollar continued its recent surge on foreign exchangemarkets, pushing bond prices to broad gains of as much as $5 forevery $1,000 in face value.   Oat futures prices rose sharply but other grain futures priceswere mixed on the Chicago Board of Trade. On other exchanges,precious metals futures fell sharply, livestock and meat futureswere mixed and energy futures slipped.</TEXT></DOC>